Pop rock icon and 17-time Grammy Award winner Sting is set to perform at the Seminole Hard Rock Hotel and Casino in Tampa at 8 p.m. May 21. Accompanied by an electric rock ensemble, and joined by special guest Joe Sumner, the star presents “My Songs,” a collection of hits from his career with the Police, and as a solo artist. Songs on the playlist include Roxanne, Every Breath You Take, Message in a Bottle and many more. Tickets start at $250 and go on sale to the general public at 10 a.m. Friday through Ticketmaster and at seminolehardrocktampa.com. Sting Fan Club members can access tickets starting at 10 a.m. Tuesday through 5 p.m. Thursday by visiting sting.com. Additionally, Tampa fans can access venue presale tickets beginning at 10 a.m. Wednesday through Seminole Hard Rock Tampa’s Twitter, Instagram or Facebook pages.